This paper is about knowledge-grounded dialogue generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to train the dialogue generation model, which makes it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) subfields. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to address the low-resource problem in training the model, which can be related to the subfields of neural networks (cs.NE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
